Intended usage: COMMON

IPF files are usually created by disk preservation tools like the software for the "KryoFlux" floppy controller card. The IPF files contain the low-level flux data of the disk and thus can be used to fully preserve the contents of a floppy disk. These files then can be used in emulators for providing the floppy disk contents to the emulated system.

